<title>INDIA: India eases controls on some industries.</title>
<headline>India eases controls on some industries.</headline>
<dateline>NEW DELHI 1997-07-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>India has abolished manufacturing licence controls on five industries and granted greater autonomy to nine large state-owned companies, Industry Minister Murasoli Maran said on Friday.</p>
<p>The controls were abolished for animal fats and oils; canned or dressed fur skins; asbestos; plywood and similar products, and paper and newsprint, Maran told a news conference.</p>
